      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.YMGOKoZtKgJqIsAD]{Mechanic Trick}</p>\n<p>Your @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.uWZ3LvxQ3yezLB4j]{custom rig} can exercise delicate control over your vehicle, which gains an @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JournalEntry.dXoXgaKcx2ZfBD4M.JournalEntryPage.vvdxnbL44YQeOOxr#autopilot]{autopilot} function (Core Rulebook 280) with a Piloting bonus equal to 4 + 1-1/2 the vehicleâ€™s item level. You can use your custom rig control the autopilot at a range of 500 feet, allowing you to engage, disengage, or enter coordinates for the autopilot as if you were in the vehicle. This range increases to 5 miles if you have the @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.JQiKFSMXkqLMW98N]{expert rig} ability, 50 miles if you have the advanced rig ability, and has a planetary range if you have the @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.GLFInMDKp2fLRpsG]{superior rig} ability.</p>\n<p>You must have the @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.lOB5gR1uyuadv0kI]{experimental vehicle} class feature to choose this trick.</p>"
